{"fsPath":"/home/khanh/src/0_github/leetcode/prep/vulcan/01_system_design/SYS-chat-messaging/impl/DESIGN_TECHNIQUES_AND_ARCHITECTURE.md","fileUuid":"e6d76aed-3fbc-4950-a501-4c61f3571faf","fileSizeBytes":11887,"numLines":442,"diffChanges":[{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":247,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":248,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":247,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":297,"addedLines":["## 7) ACK explained (what and why)","","ACK means **Acknowledgement**: a confirmation signal for a specific step in message lifecycle.","","In chat systems, ACK is used to answer these questions:","","- Has server persisted my message yet?","- Has recipient device received the message?","- Has recipient read the message?","","This project uses a 3-level ACK model:","","- `server_ack`","  - Meaning: server accepted and persisted the message.","  - Produced by: gateway response after `CreateMessage`.","  - Purpose: sender knows submit is successful and can stop retrying.","","- `delivery_ack`","  - Meaning: recipient device confirms message delivery.","  - Produced by: client sends `ack_delivery`.","  - Persisted as: `message_receipts` with `receipt_type='delivered'`.","  - Purpose: show delivered status and support delivery analytics.","","- `read_ack`","  - Meaning: recipient confirms read progress up to message X.","  - Produced by: client sends `ack_read`.","  - Persisted as:","    - `members.last_read_message_id` (monotonic pointer),","    - `message_receipts` with `receipt_type='read'`.","  - Purpose: read receipts and consistent read state across devices.","","Where this is implemented:","","- WS protocol handling:","  - [`internal/transport/ws.go`](internal/transport/ws.go)","- ACK persistence and business logic:","  - [`internal/core/service.go`](internal/core/service.go) (`RecordDeliveryAck`, `RecordReadAck`)","- ACK storage schema:","  - [`internal/db/schema.go`](internal/db/schema.go) (`message_receipts`, `members.last_read_message_id`)","","Why ACK is critical:","","- reliability under retries","- correct sent/delivered/read UX","- measurable message lifecycle latency","- idempotent state transitions under network failures","","---","","## 8) Data model walkthrough"],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000214,2,1000215,2,1000216,2,1000217,1000218,1000219,2,1000220,2,121,1000221,1000222,1000223,2,1000224,1000225,1000226,1000227,1000228,2,1000229,1000230,1000231,1000232,1000233,1000234,1000235,2,1000236,2,1000237,1000238,1000239,1000240,1000241,1000242,2,1000243,2,1000244,1000245,1000246,1000247,2,10,2,1000248]},{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":264,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":265,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":313,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":314,"addedLines":["## 9) End-to-end flow examples"],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000249]},{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":313,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":314,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":362,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":363,"addedLines":["## 10) Reliability characteristics and limitations"],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000250]},{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":335,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":336,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":384,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":385,"addedLines":["## 11) Alternatives considered (and trade-offs)"],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000251]},{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":362,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":363,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":411,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":412,"addedLines":["## 12) Code reading guide for new contributors"],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000252]},{"originalStartLineNumberOneIndexed":378,"originalEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":379,"modifiedStartLineNumberOneIndexed":427,"modifiedEndLineNumberExclusiveOneIndexed":428,"addedLines":["## 13) Operational entrypoints"],"tokenizedAddedLines":[1000253]}],"gitInfo":{"gitInfo":{"gitRoot":"/home/khanh/src/0_github/leetcode","branch":"main","commi